%20discovered%20that%20Chinese%20cities%2C%20including%20Beijing%20and%20Tianjin%2C%20are%20facing%20a%20%26quot%3Bmoderate%20to%20severe%26quot%3B%20risk%20of%20subsidence.%2045%25%20of%20China's%20urban%20land%20was%20sinking%20faster%20than%203%20millimetres%20per%20year%2C%20with%2016%25%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20over%2010%20millimetres%20per%20year%2C%20the%20study%20revealed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adl4366%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20scientists%20measured%20land%20subsidence%20in%20every%20Chinese%20city%20with%20a%20population%20of%20more%20than%202%20million%20people%20over%20the%20period%20from%202015%20to%202022.%20Of%20the%2082%20cities%20they%20examined%2C%20the%20team%20found%20that%20some%20cities%20are%20subsiding%20rapidly%2C%20with%20one%20in%20six%20exceeding%2010mm%20per%20year.%20They%20also%20found%20that%20while%20China's%20biggest%20city%20Shanghai%20continues%20to%20subside%20after%20sinking%20up%20to%203%20meters%20over%20the%20past%20century%2C%20Beijing%20is%20sinking%2045%20millimetres%20annually%20near%20its%20subways%20and%20highways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20subsidence%20appears%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20a%20range%20of%20factors%20such%20as%20groundwater%20withdrawal%20and%20the%20weight%20of%20buildings%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20the%20study%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fplanet-earth%2Fhalf-of-chinas-cities-are-sinking-putting-most-of-the-countrys-urban-population-at-risk%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHigh-rise%20buildings%20are%20sprouting%20up%2C%20road%20systems%20are%20expanding%2C%20and%20groundwater%20is%20being%20used%2C%20all%20at%20a%20rapid%20pace%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20the%20national%20pattern%20of%20city%20subsidence%2C%20we%20identified%20several%20natural%20and%20human%20factors%20that%20were%20associated%20with%20city%20subsidence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20team%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%20The%20natural%20factors%20include%20the%20geological%20setting%20of%20each%20city%20and%20the%20depth%20of%20the%20bedrock%2C%20which%20influenced%20the%20amount%20of%20weight%20the%20ground%20could%20hold%20up%20without%20sinking.%20The%20scientists%20also%20found%20a%20strong%20link%20between%20sinking%20cities%20and%20groundwater%20loss%2C%20which%20leaves%20empty%20pore%20space%20in%20the%20crust%20that%20becomes%20compacted%20as%20weight%20piles%20on%20above.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Falien-life-might-be-purple-in-colour-and-not-green-reveals-study-5476669%5C%22%3EAlien%20Life%20Might%20Be%20Purple%20In%20Colour%20And%20Not%20Green%2C%20Reveals%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%2C%20according%20to%20research%2C%20include%20urban%20transportation%20networks%2C%20as%20well%20as%20hydrocarbon%20extraction%20and%20mining.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthe%20key%20to%20addressing%20China's%20city%20subsidence%20could%20lie%20in%20the%20long-term%2C%20sustained%20control%20of%20groundwater%20extraction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20emphasised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSubsidence%20jeopardizes%20the%20structural%20integrity%20of%20buildings%20and%20critical%20infrastructure%20and%20exacerbates%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20in%20terms%20of%20flooding%2C%20particularly%20in%20coastal%20cities%20where%20it%20reinforces%20sea-level%20rise%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Nicholls%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20climate%20adaptation%20at%20the%20University%20of%20East%20Anglia%20in%20the%20UK%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20cautioned%20that%20the%20new%20findings%20reinforce%20the%20need%20for%20a%20national%20response%20even%20in%20other%20susceptible%20cities%20outside%20China.%3C%2F